	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'd like to clear up a few obvious thing people are missing. First off yes it does have a robe graphic. The creaters of this game decided that races with no pure casters i.e.: barbs, trolls, ogres, half-elves, wood-elves, dwarves, and half-lings. were not going to get a robe graphic. So thats why it looks like what it does on those peps. Secondly, I always considered sense I left The Realm, that all people could wear robes. When I got to EQ only pure casters could. Then monks eventually then clerics. Clerics from the start should have been able to wear them, except dwarfs, and half-lings. Because priests and robe just go together. I've always asked them to put a robe or several robes in the game that would let all people with robe graphics could wear. Im sure role-playing would go up much more. (It would with me anyway). Now finnaly they have one, but look you have to be 40+ to get it, thats a bit wrong dont you think. They should make some that are craftable and have no real stats except AC.<br>Thers my 2cp on this subject :P<br><br>Danth Questguardian<br>Order of the Helping Hand<br>Xegony<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
